spi: drain the queues in the worker + last-instant readiness check

Two host-side robustness fixes for transaction loss, both field-
debugged on an F1C200s (suniv) host where the timing differs from the
Raspberry Pi reference:

1. The SPI worker serviced exactly ONE transaction per invocation,
   while queue_work() calls coalesce whenever a run is already
   pending. Under bursts the worker gets fewer invocations than there
   are transactions; a queued TX then waits for a handshake EDGE that
   never comes (the line is already high). Signature: first scan fine,
   every later command times out; handshake high / data-ready low with
   the frame still queued; printk delays made it vanish. Fix: loop
   until there is nothing to send, nothing pending, or not-ready.

2. The ESP can deassert the handshake between the check at the top of
   the loop and the actual transfer; transacting against a not-ready
   slave silently loses the frame. Signature: cmd_mgmt_request/
   cmd_set_ie timeouts exactly during assoc bursts (a phone joining
   the SoftAP). Fix: re-check the handshake immediately before
   spi_sync_transfer and requeue the TX at the head of its priority
   queue instead of transmitting into the void.

Validated on hardware: five consecutive scans (16-17 SSIDs, zero
timeouts) and hostapd reaching AP-ENABLED on the NG cfg80211 AP path.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>

--- a/esp_hosted_ng/host/spi/esp_spi.c
+++ b/esp_hosted_ng/host/spi/esp_spi.c
@@ -293,6 +293,7 @@
 	int ret = 0;
 	volatile int trans_ready, rx_pending;
 
+next_transaction:
 	trans_ready = gpio_get_value(HANDSHAKE_PIN);
 	rx_pending = gpio_get_value(SPI_DATA_READY_PIN);
 
@@ -379,6 +380,25 @@
 	}
 #endif
 
+	/* Last-instant readiness check: the ESP may have deasserted the
+	 * handshake between the check at the top of the loop and here --
+	 * transacting against a not-ready slave silently loses the frame
+	 * (field signature: cmd_mgmt_request timeouts under assoc bursts).
+	 * Requeue and let the next handshake edge retry. */
+	if (!gpio_get_value(HANDSHAKE_PIN)) {
+		struct esp_payload_header *reh =
+			(struct esp_payload_header *)tx_skb->data;
+		if (reh->if_type == ESP_INTERNAL_IF)
+			skb_queue_head(&spi_context.tx_q[PRIO_Q_HIGH], tx_skb);
+		else if (reh->if_type == ESP_HCI_IF)
+			skb_queue_head(&spi_context.tx_q[PRIO_Q_MID], tx_skb);
+		else
+			skb_queue_head(&spi_context.tx_q[PRIO_Q_LOW], tx_skb);
+		atomic_inc(&tx_pending);
+		dev_kfree_skb(rx_skb);
+		return;
+	}
+
 	ret = spi_sync_transfer(spi_context.esp_spi_dev, &trans, 1);
 	if (ret) {
 		esp_err("SPI Transaction failed: %d", ret);
@@ -390,6 +410,15 @@
 			dev_kfree_skb(rx_skb);
 
 		dev_kfree_skb(tx_skb);
+
+		/* Drain until idle: queue_work() calls coalesce while a run
+		 * is pending, so a single-shot worker loses transactions
+		 * under bursts -- a queued TX then waits for a handshake
+		 * EDGE that never comes (the line is already high). Loop
+		 * until there is nothing to do or the ESP is not ready. */
+		tx_skb = NULL;
+		rx_skb = NULL;
+		goto next_transaction;
 	}
 }
 
